OL,3,C'Revolutionary' device to tackle acid
OL,4,Creflux given to first UK patients
OL,6,FA "revolutionary" method to treat
OL,7,Fsevere acid reflux has been implanted
OL,8,Fin patients for the first time, which
OL,9,Fcould help tackle an issue that
OL,10,Fimpacts 20% of the UK's adult
OL,11,Fpopulation.
OL,13,FUniversity Hospital Southampton (UHS)
OL,14,Fand Imperial College London have
OL,15,Fbecome the first NHS trusts in the
OL,16,Fcountry to install the device called
OL,17,Fthe RefluxStop, with Southampton being
OL,18,Fthe first to use robotic surgery for
OL,19,Fthe procedure.
