OL,3,C'Revolutionary' device to tackle acid
OL,4,Creflux given to first UK patients
OL,6,FKnown as gastro-oesophageal reflux
OL,7,Fdisease (GORD), the condition occurs
OL,8,Fwhen contents from the stomach flow
OL,9,Fback into the oesophagus ` the long
OL,10,Ftube that carries food from the throat
OL,11,Fto the stomach.
OL,13,FIt happens when the muscular valve `
OL,14,Fthe lower oesophageal sphincter ` at
OL,15,Fthe bottom of the oesophagus becomes
OL,16,Fweakened because it has moved too
OL,17,Fclose to the diaphragm or even into
OL,18,Fthe chest which affects its function
OL,19,Fto allow food in and stop acid leaking
OL,20,Fout.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
